'''''Noro lim, noro lim, Asfaloth!''''' is a [[Sindarin]] phrase cried by [[Glorfindel]] to [[Asfaloth]] while helping [[Frodo Baggins]] to escape from the [[Black Riders]]. Glorfindel had halted from his horse, telling Frodo to run, but as the hobbit was relucting, Glorfindel commanded the horse in the elf-tongue, making Asfaloth run at once right before the Riders appeared.<ref>{{FR|I12}}, p. 213</ref> 

The phrase means "run swift, run swift, Asfaloth", from imperative ''[[nor-]]'' ("run") and ''[[lim]]'' ("quick, swift").<ref>{{PE|17}}, p. 18</ref>
